panels.description: Number of builds executed in the selected time range

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  DATE_ADD(date(finished_date), INTERVAL -DAYOFMONTH(date(finished_date))+1 DAY) as time,
  count(distinct case when result = 'SUCCESS' then id else null end) as successful_build_count,
  count(distinct case when result != 'SUCCESS' then id else null end) as failed_build_count
FROM cicd_pipelines
WHERE
  -- $__timeFilter(finished_date)
   id like "%jenkins%"

  -- the following condition will remove the month with incomplete data
  -- and finished_date >= DATE_ADD(DATE_ADD($__timeFrom(), INTERVAL -DAY($__timeFrom())+1 DAY), INTERVAL +1 MONTH)
GROUP BY 1

panels.title: Deployment Frequency

panels.description: Number of builds executed in the selected time range

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  DATE_ADD(date(committed_date), INTERVAL -DAYOFMONTH(date(committed_date))+1 DAY) as time,
  SUM(additions) - SUM(deletions) as LOC
FROM commits
-- WHERE
  -- $__timeFilter(committed_date)

  -- the following condition will remove the month with incomplete data
  -- and finished_date >= DATE_ADD(DATE_ADD($__timeFrom(), INTERVAL -DAY($__timeFrom())+1 DAY), INTERVAL +1 MONTH)
GROUP BY 1

panels.title: Change Volume

panels.description: Number of builds executed in the selected time range

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
    (SELECT (SUM(CASE WHEN result = 'FAILURE' AND id LIKE '%jenkins%' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / COUNT(*)) * 100
     FROM cicd_pipelines
     WHERE created_date >= '2023-09-30 00:00:00.000' AND created_date < '2023-10-05 00:00:00.000') AS last_week,
    
    (SELECT (SUM(CASE WHEN result = 'FAILURE' AND id LIKE '%jenkins%' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / COUNT(*)) * 100
     FROM cicd_pipelines
     WHERE created_date >= '2023-09-01 00:00:00.000' AND created_date < '2023-10-10 00:00:00.000') AS this_week,

    (SELECT (last_week - this_week)) AS result;

panels.description: Number of builds executed in the selected time range

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
    (SELECT AVG(TIMESTAMPDIFF(MINUTE, created_date, resolution_date))
    FROM
    issues
    WHERE
    resolution_date IS NOT NULL
    AND created_date >= '2023-10-09 06:07:08.000'
    AND created_date < '2023-10-24 06:36:00.000') AS last_week,

    (SELECT AVG(TIMESTAMPDIFF(MINUTE, created_date, resolution_date))
    FROM
    issues
    WHERE
    resolution_date IS NOT NULL
    AND created_date >= '2023-10-09 06:36:00.000'
    AND created_date < '2023-10-24 06:59:14.794') AS this_week,

    (SELECT (last_week - this_week)) AS result;

panels.description: Number of builds executed in the selected time range

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  (SELECT AVG(duration_sec) FROM cicd_pipelines WHERE created_date >= '2023-09-27 00:00:00.000' AND created_date < '2023-10-03 00:00:00.000' AND result = 'SUCCESS' AND id LIKE "%jenkins%") AS last_week,
  (SELECT AVG(duration_sec) FROM cicd_pipelines WHERE created_date >= '2023-10-06 00:00:00.000' AND created_date < '2023-10-10 00:00:00.000' AND result = 'SUCCESS' AND id LIKE "%jenkins%") AS this_week,
  (SELECT (this_week - last_week)) AS result;

panels.description: Number of builds executed in the selected time range

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  (ABS((SELECT COUNT(*)
        FROM issues
        WHERE created_date >= '2023-10-09 06:07:08.000'
        AND created_date < '2023-10-24 06:18:00.000') -
       (SELECT COUNT(*)
        FROM issues
        WHERE created_date >= '2023-10-09 06:18:00.000'
        AND created_date < '2023-10-24 06:36:00.000')) * 100 /
       (SELECT COUNT(*)
        FROM issues
        WHERE created_date >= '2023-10-09 06:07:00.000'
        AND created_date < '2023-10-24 06:44:00.000')) AS last_week,
  (ABS((SELECT COUNT(*)
        FROM issues
        WHERE created_date >= '2023-10-09 06:36:08.000'
        AND created_date < '2023-10-24 06:45:00.000') -
       (SELECT COUNT(*)
        FROM issues
        WHERE created_date >= '2023-10-09 06:45:00.000'
        AND created_date < '2023-10-24 06:59:00.000')) * 100 /
       (SELECT COUNT(*)
        FROM issues
        WHERE created_date >= '2023-10-09 06:36:00.000'
        AND created_date < '2023-10-24 06:59:00.000')) AS this_week,
  (SELECT (this_week - last_week)) AS result;
